Drain the pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice; set pineapple aside. in a large bowl, combine the mayonnaise, salt, mustard, pepper and reserved pineapple juice; mix well. Fold in the rice, ham, green pepper, 1 cup of Swiss cheese, onion and pineapple. Transfer to a greased 2-qt. baking dish. Cover and bake at 350 degrees F for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until heated through and the cheese is melted.